                    How could the employee improve?
                </h3>
                <p>
                    <em>
                        From a manager’s point of view, how could you help them overcome their weaknesses?
                    </em>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ronnie consistently demonstrates a reluctance to collaborate with team members,
                    often opting to work in isolation. This lack of teamwork not only hinders
                    project progress but also affects overall team morale. Effective communication
                    and cooperation are essential for success, and the absence of these qualities is
                    becoming increasingly evident.
                </p>
                <h3>
                    Short term (6-months) actions / decisions / objectives
                </h3>
                <p>
                    <em>
                        Do you need a rapid response to address the current situation?
                    </em>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ronnie would greatly benefit from a training on teamwork to enhance
                    collaboration skills and foster a more cohesive work environment. This training
                    will equip him with the tools to effectively communicate and work alongside his
                    colleagues, ultimately improving team performance.
                </p>
                <h3>
                    Long term (&gt; 6 months) career discussion: Where does the employee
                    want to go, and how can you help them reach that goal?
                </h3>
                <p>
                    <em>
                        How do you see the employee in the future? Does your vision align with 
                        the employee’s goals?
                    </em>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ronnie has been selected to become the project manager, a role that reflects his
                    dedication and potential. To prepare him for this responsibility, he will first
                    lead a smaller project, allowing him to hone his skills in planning and team
                    management. This initial experience will provide valuable insights and build his
                    confidence. With the right guidance and support, Ronnie is poised to excel in
                    his new position.
                </p>
